r final MBH masses,\nDeltaMstar, and Lx. Almost all the time is spent at very low nuclear\nluminosities, yet one quarter of the total energy is emitted at an Eddington\nratio > 0.1. The duty-cycle of AGN activity approximates 4% (Abridged).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Aug 2016 09:13:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-25"}
